'''Tolombeh-ye Bar Aftab Shirdani''' ({{lang-fa|<U+062A><U+0644><U+0645><U+0628><U+0647> <U+0628><U+0631><U+0627><U+0641><U+062A><U+0627><U+0628> <U+0634><U+064A><U+0631><U+062F><U+0627><U+0646><U+064A>}}, also [[Romanize]]d as '''Tolombeh-ye Bar <U+0100>ft<U+0101>b Sh<U+012B>rd<U+0101>n<U+012B>''') is a village in [[Hangam Rural District (Fars Province)|Hangam Rural District]], in the [[Central District (Qir and Karzin County)|Central District]] of [[Qir and Karzin County]], [[Fars Province]], [[Iran]]. At the 2006 census, its population was 24, in 4 families.<ref>{{IranCensus2006|07}}</ref>  

